OL,3,CPolice force apologises to family of
OL,4,Cman who died after train crash
OL,6,FA police force has apologised to the
OL,7,Ffamily of a man who died when two
OL,8,Ftrains collided in mid-Wales.
OL,10,FDavid Tudor Evans, 66, died after two
OL,11,FTransport for Wales (TfW) trains
OL,12,Fcollided head on in Talerddig, near
OL,13,FLlanbrynmair in Powys at 7.26pm on 21
OL,14,FOctober.
OL,16,FNow a close family friend has accused
OL,17,Fthe British Transport Police (BTP) `
OL,18,Fwho are investigating the incident `
OL,19,Fof failing to support the family, with
OL,20,Fthe force issuing an apology on
OL,21,FThursday.
